# gh-prreview Development Rules (Python Implementation)

## Testing During Development

- **CRITICAL**: Test commands using `./run-gh-prreview-dev [command] [args...]` - runs the actual CLI from source without requiring a Nix build
  - Example: `./run-gh-prreview-dev list-awaiting`
  - Example: `./run-gh-prreview-dev checkout 12345`
  - Automatically enters `nix develop` shell with all dependencies
  - Sets up test environment variables (GH_PRREVIEW_REVIEW_PATH, etc.)
  - Requires `$MONOREPO_ROOT` environment variable to be set
  - Changes to `$MONOREPO_ROOT` directory automatically
- Run `check-all.sh` for full checks (format, lint, type checking, and tests)
  - **Must be run inside `nix develop` shell** or via `nix develop ../..#gh-prreview --command ./check-all.sh`
  - Supports flags: `--no-fix`, `--quick`, `--suppress-coverage-check`
  - Assumes all tools (ruff, mypy, pytest) are available in PATH
- Run specific tests: `python3 -m pytest tests/unit/models/test_pr.py -v` (inside nix develop shell)
- Test CLI directly: `PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m gh_prreview.cli.main --help` (inside nix develop shell)

## Code Quality

- All code must pass ruff formatting: `ruff format src tests`
- All code must pass ruff linting: `ruff check src tests`
- All code must pass mypy type checking: `mypy src`
- Maintain 80%+ test coverage (checked by pytest)

## Python Guidelines

- Use `from __future__ import annotations` at the top of every module for Python 3.9+ compatibility
- Use type hints on all function signatures
- Use Protocol classes for dependency injection (enables easy mocking in tests)
- Use dataclasses for models (frozen=True when immutable)
- Prefer async/await for GitHub API calls

## Structure

- `src/gh_prreview/` - Source code
  - `models/` - Data models (Config, PR, Review, Worktree)
  - `services/` - Services (GitHub API, Git, Config, Output)
  - `commands/` - Command implementations
  - `cli/` - Click CLI entry point
- `tests/` - Test code
  - `unit/` - Unit tests (test individual components)
  - `integration/` - Integration tests (test CLI end-to-end)
  - `conftest.py` - Shared fixtures

## Documentation

- README.md MUST be updated after significant changes
- Docstrings required for all public functions and classes
- Keep MIGRATION_COMPLETE.md updated with any architectural changes

## Version Management

- Version is in `pyproject.toml` and `src/gh_prreview/__init__.py`
- Nix build auto-generates version with date and git hash
- Follow semantic versioning (major.minor.patch)

## Common Development Tasks

```bash
# Run CLI from source (with test config, no Nix build required)
# Requires: export MONOREPO_ROOT=/path/to/monorepo
./run-gh-prreview-dev list-awaiting      # Test list-awaiting command
./run-gh-prreview-dev list-awaiting --deep
./run-gh-prreview-dev list-local         # Test list-local command
./run-gh-prreview-dev checkout 12345     # Test checkout command
./run-gh-prreview-dev remove 12345       # Test remove command

# Full checks before commit (run from nix develop shell)
nix develop ../..#gh-prreview --command ./check-all.sh  # Auto-fix mode (default)
nix develop ../..#gh-prreview --command ./check-all.sh --no-fix  # Check-only mode (for CI)
nix develop ../..#gh-prreview --command ./check-all.sh --quick  # Skip slow checks

# Or enter the shell first, then run check-all.sh
nix develop ../..#gh-prreview
./check-all.sh                      # Now you can run directly

# Run pytest tests (inside nix develop shell)
python3 -m pytest tests/unit -v                      # All unit tests
python3 -m pytest tests/unit/services/test_github.py -v  # Specific test
python3 -m pytest --cov=gh_prreview --cov-report=html     # With coverage

# Enter development shell manually
nix develop ../..#gh-prreview

# Test CLI directly (inside nix develop shell)
PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m gh_prreview.cli.main --help
PYTHONPATH=src python3 -m gh_prreview.cli.main list-local
```

## Development Environment

- Development shell is defined in root `flake.nix` as `devShells.gh-prreview`
- Includes Python 3.11, pytest, mypy, ruff, gh, git, and all Python dependencies
- Both `run-gh-prreview-dev` and `check-all.sh` automatically enter the dev shell
- Manual entry: `nix develop ../..#gh-prreview`

## Environment Variables

- **Required**: `MONOREPO_ROOT` - Path to the monorepo (used by `run-gh-prreview-dev`)
- **Auto-set by run-gh-prreview-dev**:
  - `GH_PRREVIEW_REVIEW_PATH=/tmp/gh-prreview-test-reviews`
  - `GH_PRREVIEW_OLD_PR_DAYS=30`
  - `GH_PRREVIEW_WATCH_LABELS=team/alpha,team/beta`
  - `GH_PRREVIEW_WATCH_USERS=user1,user2,user3`

## Notes

- Temporary test scripts should be removed once the problem is solved
- **CRITICAL**: Testing and debugging should use `./run-gh-prreview-dev [command]` rather than rebuilding with Nix repeatedly
- Pre-commit hooks automatically run `check-all.sh` when gh-prreview files are staged
- CI uses `nix flake check` which runs `checks.test-gh-prreview` (calls `check-all.sh --no-fix --quick --suppress-coverage-check`)
